The paper is about techniques to characterize the importance of data in a recommender system, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses privacy and data management, which are topics related to security and privacy (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents a new attribute called user hardship, which is particularly relevant to location datasets, and this could potentially fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
